@abdosi modified the macsec/test_interop_protocol.py test_snmp to send SNMP query from neighboring vsonic/ceos devices to SONiC DUT. This way we can have the test running on multi-asic device as well.

While testing out on multi-asic device, found that there might be additional changes required. 
So will keep the skip for multi-asic as is in this PR and raise another PR with changes required for multi-asic.

@StormLiangMS @kevinskwang for visible
As agreed at last weekly meeting,
to better manage PR, recommended to split this change into multiple small PR to merge if possible.

@bingwang-ms : I understand. When I see endless loop, it only means the dst_port_ip is not directed to the intended dst_port_id at all. That is when we see the infinite loop. It shouldn't happen unless there is a problem in the DUT, or there is a mismatch in the arguments to the ptf call.

I will add a check to stop the infinite loop after 500 ip addresses, if that is ok. If none of the 500 src addresses work(the dst_port_id never got any of the packets, but there is other ports receive all the packets), then this is a problem, and a RuntimeError will be raised.

It will help me if you can provide the topology (t0/t1/t1-lag/t2).

@rraghav-cisco 

Could you please to prepare a new PR to quickly fix this infinite loop issue by check max loop count ASAP?

